result.execSummary:
The defendant Shanita S McMurtry was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Shanita S McMurtry is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Shanita S McMurtry was found guilty of Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
AS to counts 1 and 2, court orders counts dismissed.
AS to count 3:   Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, and further advised that if not a United States citizen deportation is possible. Defendant examined as to plea, and entered a plea of guilty.  Court found defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived all constitutional rights. Plea questionnaire waiver of rights and addendum to plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulated to the criminal complaint as factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the AMENDED Information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered into the record.  
Sentencing proceeded.  State advised the Court they have complied with the Victims' Rights Law.  Statements by parties.  The Court ordered the Defendant to serve 66 days in the House of Correction, with credit for 66 days time served.  
Court orders that all costs, assessments and surcharges be paid during period of probation imposed in 13CF4434 and failure to do so will result in civil judgment.
Appeal rights given.
